snippet.textDisplay:
I'm not even a Billie Eilish fan. Not saying she makes bad music at all, just that it's not my thing. I am, however, a fan of the positive she tries to put out there.

It's clear though that plenty of people missed the point entirely. People in the comments judging her actions, yet again, by how much or how little she showed, and basing her worth, and the worth of her message, on that alone. Sure, she didn't want to be judged by her body before, and that is no less meaningful than as it is now. However, she is transitioning to an adult and expressing the lessons she's learned through her fame, that her body, shown or covered, is being used against others, not only herself. Shaming her for covering too much, shaming others for not covering enough. She's already proven that her fame didn't come from her body, and now that people think her style is locked in, she's shaking things back up by saying that style does not, in fact, define her.
